(746, 1, '2021-12-12 08:42:29', '2021-12-12 08:42:29', 'From the onset, It is important to note that the \"modern\" and \"contemporary\" are two different interior styles. A modern interior design styleis defined by clean and simple color schemes. welcoming feel, clean individual elements, as well as heavy use of glass and steel and much needed siding replacements that date back in historical times. Black and white dominate the color palette, with some shaded fades blue, red, among other prime colors.\r\n\r\nwe spoke aboiut contemporary interior design style which blends the design styles from various eras. The modern style design is from a specific period - the dawn of the 20th century. this style is rooted in German and Scandinavian design styles and architecture. it is all about logic and practicality and the paintings and sculptures are chosen accordingly. The focus of the designer is on functionality and NOT on the form.', 'Modern Interior Design Style', '', 'trash', 'open', 'open', '', 'first-blog-us-2__trashed', '', '', '2021-12-28 16:37:35', '2021-12-28 16:37:35', '', 0, 'http://localhost/hexagon-wordpress/?p=746', 0, 'post', '', 0);
